title: BREAKING: Senate votes In Favor (38-28) to legalize Sunday liquor sales in MN | The KFAN Bits Page | KFAN FM 100.3
text:
— Sam Sansevere (@samsansevere) February 27, 2017 Historic Vote: Minnesota Senate votes 38-28 to legalize Sunday liquor store sales for first time. — Patrick Kessler (@PatKessler) February 27, 2017 MN House, Senate have now voted to legalize Sunday liquor store sales for first time in state history. Differences betw bills to work out. — Patrick Kessler (@PatKessler) February 27, 2017 
Governor Dayton has already said that he will not veto the bill meaning that Minnesotans will no longer need to cross the border to buy booze on Sundays.
